dsxT1E1MIB.description: Interface MIB definitions for Tiara T1/E1 interface modules.

dsxT1E1IfConfigLineTable.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigLineTable
dsxT1E1IfConfigLineTable.description: A list of T1/E1 interfaces currently configured.

dsxT1E1IfConfigLineEntry.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigLineEntry
dsxT1E1IfConfigLineEntry.description: An entry containing configuration for each T1/E1 interface.

dsxT1E1IfIndex.name: dsxT1E1IfIndex
dsxT1E1IfIndex.description: An integer value which is an index in to the entries of ifTable (MIB-II) whose interface type is ds1

dsxT1E1IfConfigServiceMode.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigServiceMode
dsxT1E1IfConfigServiceMode.description: Indicates the T1/E1 interface is in service if it is TRUE.

dsxT1E1IfConfigLineMode.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigLineMode
dsxT1E1IfConfigLineMode.description: Line Mode for this T1/E1 interface

dsxT1E1IfConfigLineType.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigLineType
dsxT1E1IfConfigLineType.description: This variable indicates the variety of T1/E1 interpretation of the usage and error statistics. The values, in sequence, describe: TITLE: SPECIFICATION: esf Extended SuperFrame DS1 d4 AT&T D4 format DS1 --*************************************************************************** -- Added by Smita , Wipro Technologies, to incorporate an OE1 card e1-MF G.704 (Table 4a) with TS16 multiframing enabled e1-CRC-MF G.704 (Table 4b) with TS16 multiframing enabled

dsxT1E1IfConfigLineCode.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigLineCode
dsxT1E1IfConfigLineCode.description: This variable describes the variety of Zero Code Suppression used on the link, which in turn affects a number of its characteristics. b8zs refers to the use of a specified pattern of normal bits and bipolar violations which are used to replace a sequence of eight zero bits. ami refers to a mode wherein no zero code suppression is present and the line encoding does not solve the problem directly. In this application, the higher layer must provide data which meets or exceeds the pulse density re- quirements, such as inverting HDLC data. --************************************************************************ -- Added by Smita , Wipro Technologies, to incorporate an OE1 card E1 links, with or without CRC, use dsx1HDB3 or dsx1AMI.

dsxT1E1IfConfigLBO.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigLBO
dsxT1E1IfConfigLBO.description: Signal attenuation at 772 kHz lbo-zero-db carrier advised LBO code A 0.0 - 5.5 db lbo-75-db carrier advised LBO code B 7.5 - 13.0 db lbo-15-db carrier advised LBO code C 15.0 - 22.0 db lbo-12-db carrier advised LBO code for E1 short haul lbo-43-db carrier advised LBO code for E1 long haul This variable can be set only for CSU linemode

dsxT1E1IfConfigCableLength.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigCableLength
dsxT1E1IfConfigCableLength.description: This variable specifies the length of the cable in feet.

dsxT1E1IfConfigRaiAlarm.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigRaiAlarm
dsxT1E1IfConfigRaiAlarm.description: Configurition of Remote Alarm Indication Alarm generation and detection.

dsxT1E1IfConfigTransmitClock.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigTransmitClock
dsxT1E1IfConfigTransmitClock.description: The source of Transmit Clock. 'timing-line' indicates that the recovered re- ceive clock is used as the transmit clock. 'timing-internal' indicates that a local clock source is used.

dsxT1E1IfConfigTimeSlotMap.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigTimeSlotMap
dsxT1E1IfConfigTimeSlotMap.description: Time slot map of the T1/E1 line that are being used if it is used corresponding bit position is set.

dsxT1E1IfConfigCableType.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigCableType
dsxT1E1IfConfigCableType.description: The cable type that is being used. 'cable-type-coax' indicates that the cable is coaxial and the impedance is 75 ohm 'cable-type-twistedpair' indicates that the cable is a twisted pair and the impedance is 120 ohm.

dsxT1E1IfConfigFdlTable.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigFdlTable
dsxT1E1IfConfigFdlTable.description: A list of T1/E1 interface currently configured.

dsxT1E1IfConfigFdlEntry.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigFdlEntry
dsxT1E1IfConfigFdlEntry.description: Configurable Facility Data Link (FDL) field for enable/disable the FDL utility on T1/E1 interface.

dsxT1E1IfConfigFdl.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigFdl
dsxT1E1IfConfigFdl.description: The configuration FDL type fdl-ansi-only - only supports ANSI FDL , fdl-att-only only supports ATT FDL, fdl-ansi-att supports both ANSI and ATT FDL.

dsxT1E1IfConfigFdlCsuDsuType.name: dsxT1E1IfConfigFdlCsuDsuType
dsxT1E1IfConfigFdlCsuDsuType.description: The configuration of the type of equipment fdl-csu - responds to only CSU FDL requests fdl-dsu - responds to only DSU FDL requests fdl-csudsu - responds to both CSU and DSU requests.

dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigTable.name: dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigTable
dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigTable.description: A list of T1/E1 interface alarm threshold configuration parameters.

dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigEntry.name: dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigEntry
dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigEntry.description: An entry containing alarm configuration parameters for each T1/E1 interface.

dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigSamplingInt.name: dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigSamplingInterval
dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigSamplingInt.description: Sampling Interval is the time between each sampling period.

dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigSampleType.name: dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigSampleType
dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigSampleType.description: Threshold Alarm: Sampling type sample-absolute - compares the monitored variable value againist the thresholds, sample-delta - compares the monitored variable value change from previous interval against thresholds.

dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigStartupType.name: dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigStartupType
dsxT1E1IfAlarmThresholdConfigStartupType.description: Threshold Alarm :if TRUE the first sample will be ignored if thresholds are crossed.

dsxT1E1IfTestConfigType.name: dsxT1E1IfTestConfigType
dsxT1E1IfTestConfigType.description: Test type. Specifies the type of test to execute on this T1/E1 interface. To perform no-test, payload-loopback-test, line-loopback-test only TestType is mandatory. To perform pattern-test, ConfigTime and ConfigPattern are mandatory. To perform remote-lpup-test and remote-lpdn-test, ConfigLoopCode is mandatory

dsxT1E1IfTestConfigTime.name: dsxT1E1IfTestConfigTime
dsxT1E1IfTestConfigTime.description: Test time. when set to 0, test time is unlimited. Otherwise duration of test, specified in seconds.

dsxT1E1IfTestConfigPattern.name: dsxT1E1IfTestConfigPattern
dsxT1E1IfTestConfigPattern.description: Bit Pattern type used in testing T1/E1 for Pattern Test.

dsxT1E1IfTestConfigLoopCode.name: dsxT1E1IfTestConfigLoopCode
dsxT1E1IfTestConfigLoopCode.description: Type of loopcode is used for loopback test.

dsxT1E1IfStatusLineStatus.name: dsxT1E1IfStatusLineStatus
dsxT1E1IfStatusLineStatus.description: The summary of the status RRAIStatus - Recieve RAI (Recieve Alarm Indication), TRAIStatus - Transmit RAI , RLOSStatus - Recieve Loss Of Sync, RISStatus - Recieve Idle Signal REXZStatus - Recieve Excessive Zeros, LORCStatus - Loss Of Recive Clock (LORC), TDEStatus - transmit pulse density, SendLineCode - transmit linecode SendPayLoadCode - transmit paylode code SendResetCode - transmit reset code, SendTE1Code - transmit T1/E1 linecode, SendPattern - transmit T1/E1 Pattern, RcvTestCode - recive test code, LoopbackStatus - Status of Loop back, TAISStatus - Transmit Alarm Indication Siganl, RAISStatus - Recieve Alarm Indication Signal, LOFStatus - Loss Of Frame.

dsxT1E1IfStatusTransmitClock.name: dsxT1E1IfStatusTransmitClock
dsxT1E1IfStatusTransmitClock.description: The source of Tranmit Clock. 'timing-line' indicates that the recovered re- ceive clock is used as the transmit clock. 'timing-internal' indicates that a local clock source is used.

dsxT1E1IfAlarmStatusTable.name: dsxT1E1IfAlarmStatusTable
dsxT1E1IfAlarmStatusTable.description: A list of T1/E1 interface alarm status entries

dsxT1E1IfAlarmStatusEntry.name: dsxT1E1IfAlarmStatusEntry
dsxT1E1IfAlarmStatusEntry.description: An entry containing alarm status for each T1/E1 interface.

dsxT1E1IfAlarmStatusAlarmStatus.name: dsxT1E1IfAlarmStatusAlarmStatus
dsxT1E1IfAlarmStatusAlarmStatus.description: Alarm Status of T1/E1 interface. RRAI - Recieve Rx Alarm Indication, TRAI - Transmit Rx Alarm Indication, RAIS - Recieve Alarm Indication Signal, TAIS - Transmit Alarm Indication Signal, RLOF - Recieve Loss Of Frame, RLOS - Recieve Loss Of Signal, Loopback - if looped back state is true, RIS - Recieve Idle Signal, REXZ - Recieve Excessive Zeros, RFEBE - Recieve Far End Block Error, RPE - Recieve Parity Error, RCPE - Recieve C-Parity Error, LORC - Loss Of Recieve Clock, TPDE - Transmit Pulse DEnsity, TFEBE - Transmit Far End Block Error, ibTest - InBand Test running if true.

dsxT1E1IfAlarmStatusThresholdStatus.name: dsxT1E1IfAlarmStatusThresholdStatus
dsxT1E1IfAlarmStatusThresholdStatus.description: Status of the user configurable threshold Alarms 1 means present.
